</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 6:14
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='363768' id='t-363768'>In our day, we have digitization. That strips all the physical mass out of information,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='368359' id='t-368359'>so now it's almost zero cost to copy and share information.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='371764' id='t-371764'>Our printing press is the Internet. Our coffee houses are social networks.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='376001' id='t-376001'>We're moving to what I would think of as a fully connected system,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='381103' id='t-381103'>and we have global decisions to make in this system,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='383976' id='t-383976'>decisions about climate, about finance systems,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='387662' id='t-387662'>about resources. And think about it --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='391003' id='t-391003'>if we want to make an important decision about buying a house,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='393465' id='t-393465'>we don't just go off. I mean, I don't know about you,</span>
